What changed and why (short)
- Added a Scheduling UI (start datetime, slot duration, break, parallel slots, group-by) and a Generate Schedule button so the site can auto-assign screening times based on your rules.
- CSV import now recognizes FirstName/MiddleName/LastName/Name columns, maps them into row.first_name, row.middle_name, row.last_name, and row.name; if the CSV only contains a single name field it's split into parts.
- The email template supports placeholders for first/middle/last names and fills them from the row object so personalized emails are produced.
- Removed the preview feature per your instruction.
- Kept all original features (import/export/add/delete/edit/send/log/progress) and added console logging and better error handling.

Testing tips
1. Use the Download Template button to get a sample with FirstName/MiddleName/LastName and Name columns.
2. Fill Scheduling settings (Start Date & Time is required), then either import a CSV (with Auto assign checked) or import and click Generate Schedule to see datetimes populate.
3. Verify emails by entering your Brevo API key and a test recipient address; send and check results in the in-page log and browser console.

